						<div class="postbody">Possible bug report:<br /><br />A VRC6 (mapper 24) ROM I made a while back:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://rainwarrior.ca/music/sundried.nes">http://rainwarrior.ca/music/sundried.nes</a><!-- m --><br /><br />The PPU viewer says &quot;horizontal&quot; mirroring but is incorrectly showing the result of vertical mirroring. (This was the first ROM I ever made, but it doesn't fail on any other emulator I know of.)<br /><br /><em>Edit: apparently the fault was my ROM, but it was not exposed by several emulators I had tried it with due to obscurity of implementation. See below.<br />ROM has been updated, used to initialize $B003 with $04, now uses $24.</em><br /><br /><br />BTW being able to select font for the disassembly is fantastic. I can easily see twice as many lines in there now.</div>

					
